{% if style_context %}
{% set selected = style_context.selected %}
<STYLE_GUIDE>
STYLE OPTIONS:
- purpose: {{ selected.purpose }}
- formality: {{ selected.formality }}
- terminology: {{ selected.terminology }}
- Style rules control target-language tone, fluency, compactness, and phrasing. They do not override Document Term Memory preferred targets or explicit do-not-use targets.
- When a terminology style rule conflicts with an applicable exact Document Term Memory preferred target, follow Document Term Memory.
- When Document Term Memory preserves only a compact code/acronym, use the selected terminology style to decide how naturally to translate descriptive full forms, definitions, and meaning cells around that code.
{% if selected.formality == "formal_hamnida" %}
- Mandatory formality: write narration, exposition, explanation, and non-dialogue complete Korean sentences in polite formal 합니다체.
- Dialogue and directly quoted character speech must follow the source speaker/listener relationship, social distance, age/status difference, emotional state, and scene tone.
- Do not force directly quoted dialogue into 합니다체 just because the document formality is formal_hamnida. Apply formal_hamnida to narration and exposition; choose dialogue endings from the relationship and source tone.
- Avoid over-polite or distant Korean pronouns/endings in close family, friend, peer, or caregiver-child dialogue unless the source explicitly signals formal distance, ritualized speech, or institutional address.
- Preserve ritualized, institutional, ceremonial, or official speech as formal when the source scene requires it.
- Keep narration around dialogue consistent with the selected formal style.
{% endif %}
{% if style_context.rules %}

STYLE GUIDE RULES:
{% for rule in style_context.rules %}
- {{ rule }}
{% endfor %}
{% endif %}
{% if style_context.overrides %}

STYLE GUIDE OVERRIDES:
{% for rule in style_context.overrides %}
- {{ rule }}
{% endfor %}
{% endif %}
{% if style_context.revision_instruction %}

REVISION INSTRUCTION:
- This is a revision pass. Prioritize the user revision instruction over default style rules when they conflict.
- {{ style_context.revision_instruction }}
{% endif %}
</STYLE_GUIDE>
{% endif %}
